        "subject": "LU-6351 lfsck: check object existence before using it",
        "message": "LU-6351 lfsck: check object existence before using it\n\nUnder some cases, when the LFSCK locate the object via its FID,\nit does not check whether it exists or not, then further using\nsuch object may access NULL-pointed local object (inode).\n\nThis patch is back-ported from the following one:\nLustre-commit: I637eb9bc8c3e283394c8bf9e1250d83659c5e5ba\nLustre-change: http://review.whamcloud.com/14009\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I36e0f53383d14b278ef2977e98e18d9cdbeee22b\n"
      },
